Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Higher spin Compton amplitudes", "Title",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.9913698320477448`*^9, 
  3.9913698523492126`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"672a426f-5914-7d44-b32a-\
3312d34eacbb"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In this file, we compute the higher spin Compton amplitudes . We \
particularly focus on the Weinberg Minimal (",
 StyleBox["WM",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ") amplitudes which have been computed in the arxiv : 2506.12431 and \
2504.06343 . We follow the following steps :\n \n 1. Compute the Feynman \
rules\n 2. Compute the exchange diagrams\n 3. Compute the gauge \
transformation\n 4. Implement the contact term algorithm to restore gauge \
invariance . \n 5. Write the final answer in a manifestly gauge invariant \
form .\n  \n  Every function can be written in two forms : (1) Symbolic form \
and (2) Expression form . The functions come with an argument which takes two \
values ",
 StyleBox["sym",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (stands for symbolic) and ",
 StyleBox["exp",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " (stands for expression) . By default the argument is ",
 StyleBox["sym",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " . To change sym to exp, one can use the command ",
 StyleBox["ToExp",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " .  In general, any symbol with ",
 StyleBox["sym ",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["is same as the symbol itself i.e. X_[",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 StyleBox["sym",
  FontWeight->"Plain",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 StyleBox["]:=X.",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 "\n  \n",
 StyleBox["  The sections with a * must also be run but can be skipped for \
reading.",
  FontColor->RGBColor[0.8, 0.3, 0.8]]
}], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.991369854318985*^9, 3.9913699178336697`*^9}, {
  3.9913699854353256`*^9, 3.991370533798172*^9}, {3.9913705821283054`*^9, 
  3.991370661877119*^9}, {3.991370771664566*^9, 3.9913707746588154`*^9}, {
  3.991370820026943*^9, 3.991370823962185*^9}, {3.9913737041560516`*^9, 
  3.9913737398614197`*^9}, {3.991387509239153*^9, 
  3.9913875714252434`*^9}},ExpressionUUID->"94deb116-f721-c047-baaa-\
a1278be158e3"],

